phrases: Now you will be saying goodbye to your johnny, too.
Your luck ran out when you met me there.
Hello?
I am busy right now.
Fine.
We will take a little break.
Stay here and feel ashamed of yourself until I get back.
Episode 6: Eden of the East
Is this the right place to drop you?
Thanks.
It is okay if you come with me, you know.
I know, but I will go home for today.
Okay.
Bring everyone over with you, then.
I will be waiting.
Hello, Morimi residence.
Saki?
Hurry up and come home!
No.
I am too ashamed to see Ryosuke.
Come on, Ryosuke's not angry with you.
Well, I do not want to come home right now.
What are you talking about?
Where are you now, anyway?
At Micchon's
I am going to stay with her for a while, so do not worry about me.
No, you come home right now!
I am sorry.
I will call you later.
It is not like we do not know where she is,
so let us let her alone for a while.
You are too easy on her.
Got To apologize to Osugi, too.
What are you doing down there?
Would you lend me some clothes?
Eden of the East
I guess maybe this sounds fishy?
You could not call it anything but fishy!
You should probably go home for now.
If nothing else, it is hard to swallow this Takizawa's story.
And I am not sure about that outfit you are wearing, either.
What is wrong with it?
Saki looks good in anything.
And I think this Takizawa thing is actually pretty interesting.
Are you serious?
Sure, it is absurd,
but it is not like Saki living with him or not is the only issue here, right?
This club's about to hit the end of the road if nothing changes.
True.
I cannot believe this.
To think that not only our club's attention-grabber,
but the entire elite staff
would all show interest in such a dubious character!
Just what is happened with you since the graduation trip?
This behavior just does not seem worthy of the seasoned maiden
who is easily parried the come-ons of Osugi
and all the other youthful Johnnys with blood surging in their loins
for a full four years now!
Did something special happen?!
-No... -Surging blood aside,
if we would successfully started our business,
you wanted to keep Saki here come hell or high water, right, Kazuomi?
True.
After all, Eden only worked because Saki compensated for your one weakness,
your lack of leadership skills.
Now hold on.
I do not mind you criticizing my faults,
but do not you think there is a huge difference
between me and what that Takizawa person is saying?
We may have been forced into temporary withdrawal,
but I am steadily moving forward with starting the business.
Whereas he has no clothes and no memory,
and cannot remember his family, his job, or even what movies he likes.
I will not have you comparing me to someone who has absolutely nothing.
Poor boy.
I wonder if his personal.44 Magnum is still at the mercy of that cold wind...
That is not what I am asking!
Um...
Hirasawa, from what I have been hearing from in here,
I do not believe Mr. Takizawa is as worthless as you think.
He is always been gentlemanly and broad-minded towards Morimi,
and he has the drive to act, too.
His house is a shopping mall, so he seems to have some wealth,
and most importantly, there is no such thing as an evil dog owner.
I do not want your opinion!
Excuse me.
Sitting here and talking about it is pointless.
Why do not we go meet him and see what he is really like?
Agreed!
Seeing is believing.
Let us go size him up.
You have got a point, but we have to be prepared for the worst.
Let us investigate in secret first, and not just go in through the front door.
What the heck?
That is so passive.
Call it cautious!
Well, Saki?
I am fine with that.
At the time, I thought maybe I could completely believe in him,
but I am a little scared, too.
So let us all go together.
Okay.
I will go get a car.
We will leave in a half hour.
Hirasawa.
The truth is, Osugi treated me to a first-class dinner last night...
And after hearing Morimi's story,
I figured out something that I did not realize at the time.
That dinner must have been originally planned with Morimi.
What?!
Why did not you tell me sooner?!
I could not say this in front of her!
Plus, judging from how he was acting at the time,
Osugi definitely saw Morimi with Mr. Takizawa.
And what did Osugi do after dinner?
He disappeared into the night, blind drunk.
And now it seems even Morimi cannot get in touch with him...
What should we do?
We cannot leave Osugi out in the cold on such an important occasion!
True, even if he did skip out on us while he was job hunting,
he is an important charter member.
However, this is also a golden opportunity to keep Saki in Eden.
All right, find Osugi and hold him in the club room.
Roger.
This is his house?!
Are not there any other entrances?
I do not think so, because there were no homeless people inside.
This could so easily be a trap...
I guess we have got no choice.
Saki, you might be marrying into money here!
Property values around here fell pretty sharply after Careless Monday.
Now, we do not know that he bought this place after the missile strike.
Whoa, hey, hold everything!
This place is a gold mine!
Hey, look!
Look at this!
-It is so cute!
-It is so cute!
Do not go messing with those and getting us into trouble.
It looks like he is home.
Takizawa lives in the VIP room upstairs.
We have come this far, so why do not you say a few words to him as our rep?
Excuse me!
-What is wrong?
-Where is Takizawa?
Not there.
But the man's had us under surveillance all along!
Let us get out of here, now!
It is best not to get involved with such a dubious character!
Who is a dubious character?
This Takizawa person, obviously!
Yo.
Oh my, he has wings!
How cute!
This title deed is the real thing.
I just found it today, actually.
I more or less understand what you have said,
but what exactly made you decide to support our club?
And more fundamentally, what are your intentions for Saki?
No particular intentions,
I just thought there was no need for her to work for men
who would up and dump beef bowls on her.
If everyone, not just Saki, became NEETs, we could turn this country around.
Those old guys who take it for granted they are the winners
will freak out and come crying to us.
You cannot be serious.
Why not?
Did not you basically have the same idea?
I saw Eden of the East.
This is really well done.
Would you call it an image search engine?
I tried entering that miniature Shiba,
and it recognizes him no matter what angle I take a pic from.
She is the one who wrote the program.
Oh, really?
You are smart, Mittan!
She is got a sharp tongue when she is among friends,
but she is always like this with strangers.
As a kid, she never played with anyone but Hirasawa, her cousin, so...
You are cute.
I-I am not Mittan.
So if you register something on the site, any cell phone can use the info.
This is pretty cool.
Saki told me.
If you pulled off this great an invention,
it must have seemed like a good idea to turn it into a business,
so why did not that go smoothly?
I do not need you if I end up having to take care of things anyway.
I-I am so sorry!
Honestly, the road ahead is long... in a lot of ways.
-Juiz.
-Yes, this is Juiz.
I need a secretary fluent in French and Cantonese, on the double.
Accepted.
Noblesse oblige.
I sincerely pray that you, the most hardworking of CEOs,
will be an innovative savior.
You do not need to show up tomorrow, or ever again.
CEO Shiratori is in a dark mood today...
To make the story short,
we just had a little trouble
of the sort that can happen on any site or message board.
One girl had the misfortune of having to leave school,
and the university opened an investigation.
-How about this?
-That?
-Hey, I thought it was nice.
-No way.
Over here, over here.
We started out as a little recycling community,
but thanks to the development of the image recognition engine,
even near-junk turned into valuable goods.
Because Saki wrote new value into the images
that others would never have dreamed of.
Then the rest of our members copied her,
and at some point students themselves started being registered,
and people found Eden useful as a tool for finding love, too.
And that is what caused the trouble?
Yeah.
What with one thing and another, we had one member quit to look for work,
and Saki had to leave home for some reason none of us know about...
I am ashamed of how useless I am.
We are going home, guys.
Why?
Did you and Takky not come to an agreement?
I am a NEET, but I have always prided myself on being one of the best NEETs.
I do not have any special skills like Saki or Micchon,
so I have studied management and law,
to become an elite NEET that could back up other elite NEETs.
And you succeeded.
Almost, anyway.
Then what are you hung up on?
Eden of the East is a paradise for NEETs.
I do not want to get help from someone who is not a NEET.
Think of it as the jealousy of a have-not for one of the haves.
I see.
I get you... not that I understand.
What is that mean?!
As someone with no memories,
I have got my own complicated worries I cannot tell anyone about.
I am actually the one who wants your help.
What do you think?
I cannot explain the circumstances right now,
but would you help me carry out my obligations as a have?
My funding offer can be your compensation.
Please, Hirasawa.
I will prepare myself, too.
I will help run Eden with everyone.
That is that, is not it?
Saki's what troubled you the most, right?
What is left to worry about?
So in the end, I am saved by Saki again, eh?
That is no big deal, right?
Let us do a sort of give-and-take thing.
I still do not completely trust you,
but right now I will shake your hand, Mr. Takizawa.
No, from now on, I am just calling you Takizawa.
That is fine.
Let us make this a NEET paradise!
Yay!
Now that is settled!
Thank you, Takizawa.
You did not just help me, you helped everybody.
No worries.
I really like people like Hirasawa,
who are working to help other people.
Um, can I ask a question?
Why did you tell me to come to your place?
I mean, I had not told you about everyone yet.
Do you want to know?
You were looking for a change of clothes, right?
I think these would look good on you.
Micchon is playing and having fun with some guy she just met!
Though it is less like playing and more like he is messing with her.
Come on, if you do not stick it in more firmly, it will just flip over...
I cannot do it that well.
And I am not Mittan...
Hey, guys, come on out!
What have you been setting up?
Okay, here we go!
You are such a scaredy-cat, Mittan.
I am not Mittan.
Hello.
Oh, hi, Kasuga.
Have you found Osugi?
Well, it is like I kind of have, and I kind of have not.
Huh?
What do you mean?
Well, the thing is, it is possible Osugi's run into the Johnny Hunter.
The Johnny Hunter?!
I was digging around on the internet looking for him,
and I found some very interesting entries on a certain message board.
Why look for Osugi on the internet?
I know, but a man who says he is been imprisoned by a suspicious woman
has been intermittently posting cries for help
for the last eighteen hours.
It does not look like the police are doing anything yet,
but there is quite a commotion online.
And no matter how I look at it, I think this has to be Osugi.
Send me the URL of this message board.
Okay.
Rumors are that the Johnny Hunter
has already claimed a full 20,000 victims,
so it would not be odd for Osugi to be one of them.
Understood.
The night is a seal
If we mix in some bewilderment, it will end
If we are in danger of wavering, let us just abandon our reasons
We drown in dreams again
The future stretches on uncertainly
I can still forgive you, I can still know the meaning
The night exists to be listened to closely
I can copy that reason, and change
I would not mind cutting off the future to know your breath
I would not mind cutting off the future
